      <body>
         <div type="letter">
            <pb n="1" facs="Edgeworth_Beinecke_330_1812_10_30_page01.jpg"/>
            <!--filenames for photos associated with this letter. Example: <pb n="1" facs="image1.jpg image2.jpg image3.jpg"/> -->
            <opener>
               <salute> To <persName ref="./Personography.xml#MileX1">Mrs. Miles</persName>
               </salute>
            </opener>
            <p>Dear Madam I thank<lb/>
                    you for the 2 yards of<lb/>
                    edging, which are very<lb/>
                    pretty -- I am glad you<lb/>
                    have got rid of the maid<lb/>
                    servant who played us<lb/>
                    such an ingenious trick<lb/>
                    -- You may depend upon <add>it</add>
               <lb/>
                    that the first time <persName>M<hi rend="superscript">rs</hi>.<lb/>
                        Edgeworth</persName> or I have any<lb/>
                    dress commission to execute<lb/>
                    in <placeName ref="./Placeography.xml#London_ENK">London</placeName> we shall<lb/>
               <hi rend="underline">have pleasure in <choice>
                     <orig>troubl<lb/>
                        <pb n="2" facs="Edgeworth_Beinecke_330_1812_10_30_page02.jpg"/>
                        ing</orig>
                     <reg>troubling</reg>
                  </choice>
               </hi>you -- But indeed<lb/>
                    we mean if possible to<lb/>
                    live without clothes, <del/>
               <lb/>
                    or as <persName ref="./Personography.xml#MorgS1">Miss Owenson</persName> w<hi rend="superscript">d</hi>
               <lb/>
                    express it <hi rend="underline">
                  <quote>in <del>a</del> robes of<lb/>
                        thin woven air"[/underline]</quote>
               </hi> till<lb/>
                    spring, when we shall<lb/>
                    (I am told) be in <placeName ref="http://vocab.getty.edu/tgn/7011781">London</placeName>
               <lb/>
            </p>
            <closer>In the meantime<lb/>
                    I am Dear Madam<lb/>
                    Yours truly<lb/>
               <persName ref="./Personography.xml#EdgeM1">Maria Edgeworth</persName>
               <lb/>
            </closer>
            <postscript>
               <p>
                  <placeName ref="./Placeography.xml#Edgeworthstown_IE">Edgeworthstown</placeName>
                  <lb/>
                        Oct<hi rend="superscript">r</hi>. 30<hi rend="superscript">h</hi> 1812<lb/>
               </p>
            </postscript>
            <!--You can include a <pb/> here, or inside the postScript.-->
